      • addValueNow

        public void addValueNow(float value,
                        @Nonnull
                        org.joda.time.DateTime now)
        Adds a value to the managed metric collectors. Use this method instead of addValue(float) when now is determined by the caller and should be aligned with other now-related functionality. Note that now should denote the current time and cannot be an arbitrary time in the past or the future.
        Parameters:
        value - Value to add.
        now - Current time, as determined by the caller.
